  "description": "At first glance, the model does not stand out from the group of similar two-chamber refrigerators. But her secrets lie in the details. For example, full-height integrated door handles provide easy access to contents, an intuitive control panel that combines buttons and a digital display allows you to quickly set the operating mode of the device, and a replaceable antibacterial door seal prevents microbes from penetrating the Liebherr CN 4813. The equipment of the device has two separate chambers, the useful volume of which is 95 liters for the freezer and 243 liters for the refrigerator compartment. The temperature in each chamber is set independently of the other. The temperature reading in the freezer drops to -24°C during normal operation and briefly exceeds -30°C when the SuperFrost programme is selected. In addition, the refrigerator is not wasteful in terms of electricity consumption — if it complies with the A ++ class, it “winds” only 242 kW of light per year.",
